            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Memorandum ¶ Dear Sir ¶  ¶ In haste I forward you a Box containing cut flowers No 1 with green spike is an Orchid (or I think so) I had from New Caledonia and which I certainly am disappointed in bein...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.11.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Roberts</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Answ 29/11/81'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Memorandum</p>
            <table n="Table1">
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">FROM</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>JAS. F. ROBERTS,</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg>
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="font-size: 10pt; ">PRACTICAL GARDENER,</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg>
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="font-size: 10pt; ">NURSERYMAN AND SEEDSMAN,</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>YORK NURSERY,</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg>
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style="font-size: 10pt; ">UNION STREET AND COTHAM ROAD, KEW.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
                        xml:lang="en">November 26th<seg> 188</seg>1</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>To</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
                        xml:lang="en">Baron Mueller MD Ph.[D]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                           <p rend="Footnote"
                              style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                              xml:lang="en">
                              <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                              <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter missing at edge of page.</p>
                        </note>
                     </p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </table>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In haste I forward you a Box containing cut flowers No 1 with green spike is an Orchid (or I think so) I had from New Caledonia and which I certainly am disappointed in being merely of Botanical interest. No 2 is a beautiful flower springing up from the ground from a sort of spathe with no foliage lasting 2 or 3 days there are probably 10 or 12 flowers contained in this spathe probably more, as the flower fades up comes another. the foliage evidently comes after blooming as when I got the plant it had large foliage like a Calanthe or Bletia Tankervilliae (Phaius grandiflora of late date) I dont know where it originally came from the roots are tuberose not exactly like a Dahlia but the roots spring from a crown thin and then swell at the buds to tubers something like the plant I forget this moment but what in common parlance is called native Yams blooming now in the commons with blue flowers or perhaps a purple proper spikes 1/6 to 2 ft some less with fringed flowers — You will greatly oblige me by naming them for me if you can by the specimens I send you[.]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I may say that the green spike has flowered all the way up for about 5 inches but it did not occur to me to send it and Ive been so busy with rectifying what the flood &amp; hail has done for me — dreadfully Damaged Everything — allow me Dear Baron to thank you very much for the few seeds you very kindly sent me with very kind regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am dear Sir yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>ever faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James F. Roberts</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>York Nursery</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kew</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">PS. the Season has been so dreadfully dry in Queensland no rain since april that Mr Shaw could only collect a very few sorts of Orchids — untill the weather breaks up he sent me Dendrobe Caniculatum<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dendrobium canaliculatum</seg>?</p>
               </note> covered with flower &amp; some good plants of D. undulatum and a Cymbidium in fruit —</p>
         </div>
